cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.GR, cs.DS 

The paper deals with image processing techniques for removing impulsive noise from colour images while preserving edges and fine image details. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also introduces methods to speed up the filters, which involves optimization techniques and signal processing, falling under information theory (cs.IT) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves the use of order statistics, which is a statistical technique, falling under data structures (cs.DS).
